'''Bachelor of Integrated Studies''' ('''BIS''') is an [[Interdisciplinarity|interdisciplinary]] [[bachelor's degree]] offered by several universities in the [[United States]] and [[Canada]]. It allows students to design a customized and specific course of study to best suit their educational and professional objectives. Generally, this degree is sponsored by two or more [[Academic department|departments]] within the university. Schools which confer the degree include the [[University of North Texas]], [[Northern Kentucky University]], [[Utah Valley University]],<ref>[https://www.uvu.edu/is/ Integrated Studies]</ref> [[Miami University in Ohio]],<ref>[https://miamioh.edu/regionals/academics/departments/ics/academics/majors/integrative-studies/index.html Bachelor of Integrative Studies]</ref> [[Pittsburg State University]], [[George Mason University]],<ref>[https://integrative.gmu.edu/ School of Integrative Studies]</ref> [[Weber State University]], [[Washburn University]], [[Ferris State University]], [[Jacksonville State University]],<ref>[http://www.jsu.edu/degreelist.html]</ref> [[Kennesaw State University]], [[Oakland University]], [[Nevada State College]],<ref>{{cite web|url=http://nsc.nevada.edu/888.asp|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120312010520/http://nsc.nevada.edu/888.asp|title=Integrated Studies - Your Degree, Your Way.|archivedate=12 March 2012|deadurl=yes|publisher=Nevada State College|accessdate=28 February 2018}}</ref> [[Dixie State University]], and the [[University of New Brunswick]], [[Florida Gulf Coast University]], among others. 

According to materials issued by Weber State University:<blockquote>The program best suits students who have developed a sense of their educational and life goals, and who are looking for ways to express those goals through a self-designed and self-directed university program. The BIS Program serves the needs of students who want to individualize or create a unique academic program; students who want to obtain a broad [[liberal education]]; and/or students who want to prepare for specific career goals and/or [[graduate school]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://weber.edu/BIS/program.html|title=Weber State University BIS Program|author=|date=|website=weber.edu}}</ref></blockquote>

