The '''Creighton Lecture''' is an annual lecture delivered at [[King's College, London]] on a topic in history. The series, which memorializes historian and prelate [[Mandell Creighton]], began in 1907 with a grant of £650, half of which was donated by his widow, [[Louise Creighton]].<ref>{{Harvnb|Evans|2009|p=320}}</ref>
