A '''crew equipment interface test''' (CEIT) was a training procedure that helped [[spaceflight]] crewmembers gain first-hand knowledge of the flight hardware used during a space shuttle mission.<ref>. {{cite web | url = http://www.nasa.gov/mission_pages/shuttle/behindscenes/ceit_sts117_prt.htm | title = Next Crew Checks Shuttle and Payload | publisher = [[NASA]]}}</ref> For [[International Space Station]] assembly tasks, [[NASA]] conducted CEIT activities in the [[Space Station Processing Facility]] at [[Kennedy Space Center]] (KSC).<ref>{{cite web | url = http://iss.jaxa.jp/en/astro/report/2007/0706.html | title = Crew Equipment Interface Test (CEIT) for Kibo | publisher = [[JAXA]]}}</ref> The last CEIT was conducted April 7–8, 2011 by the [[STS-135]] crew involving the ''[[Space Shuttle Atlantis|space shuttle Atlantis]]'' in preparation for the final flight of the shuttle program.
