{{Infobox school | name = Colegio San Felipe | native_name = Centro Educativo de Gestion Cooperativa San Felipe | image = | image_size = | alt = | caption = | logo = | motto = | established = 1967 | closed = | type = Private | status = | category_label = | category = | gender_label = | gender = | affiliation = Formerly [[Roman Catholic|Catholic]], today non-affiliated | affiliations = | administrator = | assst_admin = | president = | chairman_label = | chairman = | rector = | principal = Miguel Ángel Kanashiro Toyama | asst principal = | campus_director = | headmaster = | head_name = Second Master | head = | head_name2 = Assistant Headmaster | head2 = | dean = | founder = | chaplain = | officer_in_charge = | faculty = | teaching_staff = | enrollment = | grades_label = | grades = Elementary and High school | streetaddress = Avenida Gregorio Escobedo 985 Jesus Maria (Lima) | city = [[Jesús María District, Lima|Jesus Maria]] | state = [[Lima]] | province = | country = {{PER}} | coordinates = | latitude = | longitude = | district = | oversight = | accreditation = | campus = | colors = [[Blue]] {{color box|#2594D3}} | colours = | athletics = | houses = | student_union = | nickname = | mascot = | free_label = [[Emblem]] | free_text = | rival = | yearbook = Anuario | newpaper = | free_label_1 = | free_1 = | free_label_2 = | free_2 = | free_label_3 = | free_3 = | test_name = | test_average = | national_ranking = | website = http://www.colegiosanfelipe.edu.pe/ | footnotes = | picture = | picture_caption = | picture2 = | picture_caption2 = }}
'''San Felipe Cooperative School''' is a K-12 private school in [[Lima]], [[Peru]]. It is located at 985 Avenida Gregorio Escobedo in the city district of [[Jesús María District, Lima|Jesús María]], and within the limits of [[Residencial San Felipe, Lima|San Felipe]] residential complex.
==History== The school was established in 1967 as [[Jesuit]] Catholic school under the religious congregation of the [[Missionary Oblates of Mary Immaculate]]. In 1969, during the military government of Gen. [[Juan Velasco Alvarado]], the religious order withdrew from the school. The parents' association then established a cooperative to run the school. This cooperative received official recognition via Government Resolution N° 007-74-DAE ORAMI IV of February 28, 1974. On July 21, 1989 under government resolution N° 1568-USE13 the school was recognized as “Centro Educativo de Gestion Cooperativa San Felipe".<ref name="San Felipe School website">[http://www.colegiosanfelipe.edu.pe/principal.php Colegio San Felipe website]</ref>
In the 1980s and 1990s, San Felipe School was well known throughout Lima, attracting students from well beyond the San Felipe area. It's being run by a parents' cooperative made it an attractive option for some on philosophical grounds.
Based on the academic performance of its graduates, San Felipe is ranked among the best schools in Peru by the respected [[Pontificia Universidad Católica del Perú]] (PUCP). As a result, San Felipe has consistently earned a spot on the list of schools whose top students seeking admission to the PUCP are exempted from the university's entrance examination.<ref>[http://www.pucp.edu.pe/content/pagina9.php?pID=216&pIDSeccionWeb=22&pIDContenedor=346&pIDIdiomaLocal=1&pIDReferencial= "ITS (Ingreso directo de alumnos destacados de colegios seleccionados) - Colegios Seleccionados"] in [http://www.pucp.edu.pe Pontificia Universidad Católica del Perú webpage] (Entry retrieved 29 January 2012).</ref><ref>[http://www.pucp.edu.pe/pregrado/postulantes/admision/modalidades-de-admision/its/colegios-seleccionados/ "ITS (Ingreso directo de alumnos destacados de colegios seleccionados) - Colegios Seleccionados - Estudio 2013"] in [http://www.pucp.edu.pe Pontificia Universidad Católica del Perú webpage] (Entry retrieved 28 August 2013).</ref><ref>Ponticifia Universidad Católica del Perú, [https://www.scribd.com/document/341796327/Colegios-ITS-PUCP-2017-Excelencia-Academica#from_embed ''Reconocimiento a la Excelencia Academica - Colegios ITS PUCP - Admisión 2017''], Lima, May 2016. (Entry retrieved 13 March 2017)</ref>
==School facilities== The school has a {{convert|58000|sqft|m2|adj=on}} facility, which in addition to classrooms, includes a paved yard with two mini-soccer pitches, one basketball court, and one volleyball court.
==Notable Graduates== * [[Germán Kino Ganoza]] ("Cherman"), graphic artist * [[Lucho Quequezana]], composer, musician<ref>[http://quequezana.blogspot.com/p/cara-cara-con-lucho.html "Cara a cara con Lucho"] (Retrieved 17 November 2012)</ref>
